#Q1.
# A database is a structured collection of data that is organized and managed to provide efficient storage, retrieval, and manipulation of data.
# SQL Databases - It follows a structured and predefined schema, known as a relational schema. Data is organized into tables with predefined columns and relationships between tables. Examples are MySQL, Oracle, etc.
# NoSQL Databases - It provide a flexible schema, allowing for dynamic and unstructured data. Data is stored in formats such as key-value pairs, documents, or graph-based structures. They are highly scalable and designed to handle large amounts of data and high traffic loads. Examples are MongoDB, Cassandra, etc.
